The paper deals with planar graph drawings, which are a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The transformations discussed in the paper involve maintaining the height of the drawing, which is a property related to data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses applications of these transformations, which could fall under discrete mathematics (cs.DM), graph theory (cs.GR), or distributed computing (cs.DC) depending on the specific application.
